Kiwi is not an ordinary fruit, it looks as nutrition material in both ways. Sticky live slices with small black seeds always do amazing things in sprinkling desserts and fruit bowls. It has a vision for eyes and fresh taste makes it a preferred choice among fruits. Originally said to be sugar, it is valuable for its medicinal properties since ancient times. Ironically, during the history, it was known as the National Fruit of New Zealand and was brought before the world in the form of 'i kiwi' r
